Dhule Municipal Corporation
Government of Maharashtra
Department of Environment and Climate Change
Government Decision No: Mission-2024 / Q. No.04 (80) / T.H.2
Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Madam Cama Marg,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032
Date: 26th of May, 2025

Read: (2) Government Decision, Environment and Climate Change Department No. Mission - 2024 / Q. No.66 / T. No.1, dated 8th February, 2022 (3) The minutes of the meeting of the Committee constituted for administrative approval held on 02nd May, 2025 are as follows:

The cash prizes to the winning local bodies in the 12 categories of Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 and the procedure for the appropriation of the prize money has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. (1). Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to give administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.
The government's decision:

Considering the points mentioned in the preamble, the total amount received by Dhule Municipal Corporation under My Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 is Rs. The works to be taken up out of the prize money of Rs. The detailed project report of the cost of 5,25,98, 725.23 (Rupees Five Crore Twenty Five Lakh Ninety Eight Thousand Seven Hundred and Twenty Five Paisa Only) has been submitted by the Commissioner, Dhule Municipal Corporation with the technical approval of the City Engineer, Dhule Municipal Corporation. The proposal The date of the committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change was taken into consideration in its meetings held on 02.05.2025. As per the recommendation made by the said committee, the total amount submitted by Dhule Municipal Corporation is Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing 5,25,98, 725.23 (Rupees Five Crore Twenty Five Lakh Ninety Eight Thousand Seven Hundred and Twenty Five Paisa Twenty Three Only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
2. Terms and Conditions:
1) Dhule Municipal Corporation will be the implementing agency for the works in this Detailed Project Report.

(2) A detailed project report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report and the physical progress report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) Expenditure in excess of the prize money should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. Under the Majhi Basundhara Abhiyan, Dhule Municipal Corporation has bagged the third position at the state level in the "Amrit Group (3 lakh to 10 lakh population)" category with a prize money of Rs. Out of the prize money of Rs. The first instalment of ₹2.50 crore has been disbursed to them. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been granted administrative approval by the Government as per paragraph 1 above. Dhule Municipal Corporation will receive the remaining prize money of Rs. The government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹2.50 crore (₹2.50 crore only) through the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
